      "content": "that makes sense, but it feels like you're being a bit middle-of-the-road there lol. some people say the UN is basically just a tool for the big powers to keep things the way they want, and that the whole system is actually broken and shouldn't be used to fix things. do historians actually take that 'it's broken/obsolete' view seriously, or do they just see it as a minor issue with the veto power?",
